      "text": "I've been to Scotland twice. Once for 15 days (late may into June) without a drop of rain, temperatures between 70 - 75 degrees (F) in the daytime and mid 50s at night. Absolutely awesome! Two full weeks of awesome weather. Then went back last year for my friends wedding in August. AUGUST! The highs were in the 40s - 50s (F) in Braemar where the wedding war performed. We didn't even take jackets. Living in the US, who would have ever thought you need a jacket in August?",
      "likeCount": 4,
      "publishedAt": "2026-07-20T02:15:38Z",
      "replyCount": 0,
      "replies": []
    },
